    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-03-13T15:14:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-03-13T15:14:00-05:00" n="92"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d92">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">422.11Am8/36: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-03-13T15:00:00-05:14">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1922—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 14—1:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>8. Department’s 6, March 1, 4 p.m.</p>
                <p>Ecuadorean Government in reply reiterates statements contained in my despatch
                    number 767 [<hi rend="italic">761?</hi>] December 1st<note n="9" xml:id="d92fn9">
                        <ref target="frus1921v01#pg_875">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1921, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 875</ref>.</note> and adds diplomatic
                    intervention only justified in case of judicial denial of justice. Full report
                    by mail.<note n="10" xml:id="d92fn10">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hartman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
